ror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Bulkeley was born about 1250, in Bulkeley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of William de Bulkeley. He had at least 1 son with Jane Le Boteler. He died in 1302, at the age of 53."},"et":{"ABT 1250–1302":"umbes 1250–1302","1250–1302":"1250–1302","1247–Female":"1247–Surnud","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1210–1312":"1210–1312","ABT 1250":"umbes 1250","1302":"1302","1247":"1247","1312":"1312","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1250":"1250","Bulkeley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bulkeley, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1250–1302":"noin 1250–1302","1250–1302":"1250–1302","1247–Female":"1247–Kuollut","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1210–1312":"1210–1312","ABT 1250":"noin 1250","1302":"1302","1247":"1247","1312":"1312","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1250":"1250","Bulkeley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bulkeley, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1250–1302":"environ 1250–1302","1250–1302":"1250–1302","1247–Female":"1247–Décédée","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1210–1312":"1210–1312","ABT 1250":"environ 1250","1302":"1302","1247":"1247","1312":"1312","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1250":"1250","Bulkeley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bulkeley, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Bulkeley est né environ 1250, à Bulkeley, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de William de Bulkeley. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Jane Le Boteler. Il est décédé en 1302, à l’âge de 53 ans."},"de":{"ABT 1250–1302":"um 1250–1302","1250–1302":"1250–1302","1247–Femal